&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3 class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Working At Bitso&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We are a diverse team that takes pride in understanding the perspectives of others. We fully embrace working remotely and we are eager to act, improve and accelerate progress inside and outside of our organization.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;To drive revolutionary changes in society and make crypto useful, we delight our customers with world-class products, deep care, and intentional empathy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The Director of Engineering for Trust &amp;amp; Safety (Guardians) owns the systems that protect every Bitso account and keep the company compliant across Mexico, Brazil, Argentina, and Colombia. The fleet covers identity and access, account protection, compliance and fraud detection, and the internal tooling that operations and compliance teams run on.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;This is a high-stakes, customer-critical fleet. When these systems fail, customers can lose access to their funds or the company can lose standing with a regulator. The Director owns reliability, security, and compliance outcomes for the fleet, leads four engineering managers, and partners closely with Product, Compliance, Security, and Fraud.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;This leader reports to the CTO and works alongside the other engineering directors. Product strategy is set with Product partners; the Director owns technical excellence, reliability, talent, and engineering standards within the fleet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Team scope&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
